headlines.description: — John Wall scored 28 points and the Houston Rockets beat the Sacramento Kings 102-94 on Saturday despite playing without an injured James Harden.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wall, Rockets beat Kings 102-94; Harden sits with injury

events.name: New York Knicks at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Austin Rivers made the go-ahead 3-pointer with 3:23 left and finished with 15 points to help the New York Knicks rally past the Indiana Pacers 106-102 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rivers helps Knicks rally late to get past Pacers 106-102

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Darius Bazley had a season-high 19 points, George Hill scored 13 of his 18 points in the third quarter and Oklahoma City beat Orlando 108-99 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder dominate second half and beat Magic 108-99

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 19 points and 14 rebounds and Tobias Harris scored 24 points to lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 127-112 win over the Charlotte Hornets on Saturday night.

— Collin Sexton scored 27 points, Andre Drummond had 12 points and 11 rebounds and the Cleveland Cavaliers wiped out a 15-point deficit in the third quarter and beat the Atlanta Hawks 96-91 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sexton, Drummond pace Cavs' rally in win over Hawks

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Eric Bledsoe capped a 19-point, 10-assist performance with a go-ahead 3-pointer in the final minute, and the New Orleans Pelicans held on for a 120-116 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bledoe, Ingram lead Pelicans past Raptors, 120-116
